I thought I’d break down some of my must have shots when I do skincare videos for brands (using a video the brand loved!)

Shots list: 
1. Packaging details - I like adding shots like these because I often use it to highlight brand name and helps position the product as the hero item - oooh especially if they have nice or unique packaging! 

2. Product application from normal to close-up - of course applying it on the video is essential BUT adding that different zoom level and making it a match cut??? 👌🤌

3. Pose with product then unbox/open - this is more for storytelling for me! Adding this makes it more personal and the opening/unboxing action adds movement. 

4. Macro texture shot - A MUST for me. I love doing macro shots on everything because it makes the video visually richhhh

5. Product application from macro to normal zoom - same as number 2 above! 

6. Split screen - not really a shot but it adds variety when editing especially if the shots are static. Also love this to show different angles at once. 

Let me know what niche I should do next below! ✨

another day another behind the scenes ;) 

I loved doing this video because it was a lil *spicy* and different than usual hehehe because I featured it as a body lotion, ofc I had to show some parts of my body and not the face! 

for those application shots, I placed a small mirror infront of my phone so I can see my screen while filming. I think it’s about time I invest on a screen mirroring device hihi 

shot this at 4k 60fps and used Capcut to edit. for a high quality vid make sure you: 

1. WIPE YOUR DAMN LENS 🤣 if your camera lens is dirty it’s so obvious on the video 
2. have HDR off
3. Have good lighting!! Sunlight is the best light but I used a studio light here. 
4. Export at the right settings - I export at 1080p 30fps (60fps if vid is super short). Some people export at 4k but for a lot of people, uploading at 4k compresses the video resulting in a mroe blurry, lower quality vid👌🏻

My macro lens, lighting and other tools are in my bio if you wanna have a look ;) Any questions drop them below!! 🫶🏻

another day another behind the scenes vid ;) 

I usually do skincare and makeup products but just wanted to show you how you also don’t need fancy equipment to do other vids ;) 

I made use of the AF lock in this shoot because the packaging looked to bright for my liking 🫠 (the contrast between the dark blue and other colours was hurting my eyes haha)

I also used some props that were already in the house (vase, ceramic stand, mirror) to make the vid a lil bit more aesthetic. 

For the shots, I alternated between 1x zoom, 2x zoom and macro shots. 

I shot this at 4k 60fps HDR off. 
If you need the link to my macro lens say “macro” in the comments and I’ll send it to you ;)

do you guys see the pattern of how I filmed this vid with multiple products? every product had: 

- 2x zoom to show it as a whole 
- macro shot to show packaging details 
- 2x zoom to show me in action open the product
- macro shot to show the formula/texture 
- and finally 2x zoom face shots for product application 

I just repeated the above for all 3 products hihi 

my favourite shot tho is the very last one with all the 3 products shown. I had to put the mirror above to brighten the space a lil bit more and avoid shadows on the products hihi

I shot this at 4k 60fps with HDR off 
and exported at 1080p 30fps
